FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE - TURKEY (THRACE) (04): OIE
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 17 Jul 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information, 13 Jul 2006, Vol. 19 - No. 28 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/A_CURRENT.HTM#Sec11>

Foot And Mouth Disease In Turkey In Thrace Region: Follow-Up Report No. 5
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Information received on 11 Jul 2006 from Dr. Huseyin Sungur, Director
General, General Directorate of Protection and Control, Ministry of
Agriculture and Rural Affairs, Ankara:
End of previous report period: 14 Jun 2006 (see Disease Information,
19 [25], 479, dated 22 Jun 2006).
End of this report period: 11 Jul 2006.
Identification of agent: foot and mouth disease virus serotype A.
Date of start of the event: 21 Jan 2006.
Details of new outbreak: On 3 Jul 2006, an outbreak in a village in
Cayirdere, Silivri district in Istanbul province resulted in 22 cases
from 1000 susceptible bovines. There were 700 susceptible ovines,
with zero cases. For location, see map at
<http://www.satelliteviews.net/cgi-bin/w.cgi?c=tu&FC=&DG=&AF=S_C&FD=Cayirdere&sdb=Go>.
Laboratory where diagnostic tests were performed: Foot and Mouth
Institute (national laboratory). ELISA test was positive on 10 Jul 2006.
